<title>UK: Ex-dividends take 2.878 points off UK's FTSE index.</title>
<headline>Ex-dividends take 2.878 points off UK's FTSE index.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>FTSE International said the following FTSE-100 stocks will go ex-dividend on Monday and the effect will be to take 2.878 points off the index at the start of trading.</p>
<p>							DIVIDEND     INDEX</p>
<p>							(PENCE)	EFFECT</p>
<p>		 COMPANY			  Net   Gross    Gross</p>
<p>     * Burmah Castrol(a)     24.80  31.000    0.383</p>
<p>     * National Grid	     6.68   8.350    0.836</p>
<p>     * United Utilities	  25.20  31.500    0.974</p>
<p>     * Vodafone		    2.45   3.063    0.548</p>
<p>     * Wolsley		     3.30   4.125    0.137</p>
<p>(a) For Burmah Castrol there is a Doreign Income Dividend (FID) of 31p only (Gross).</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
